criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with tumors that progress in size while on a watchful waiting protocol;

          -  Patients with multiple tumors;

          -  Patients with a tumor in a solitary kidney;

          -  Patients with poor renal function and a renal tumor;

          -  Patients with significant co-morbidities that may benefit from a less invasive
             approach.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Large tumors > 4.0cm;

          -  Unable to have a general anesthetic;

          -  Unable to comply with follow-up protocol (i.e., routine CT or MRI and a follow-up
             biopsy);

          -  Uncorrectable bleeding diathesis;

          -  Evidence of metastatic disease.
